1 AN ACT relating to administrative regulations for medications for substance use
2 disorder and declaring an emergency.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 13A IS CREATED TO
5 READ AS FOLLOWS:
6 (1) The General Assembly finds that the following administrative regulations and
7 any proposed amendments to the following administrative regulations are
8 deficient:
9 (a) 201 KAR 9:270, Professional standards for prescribing, dispensing, or
10 administering Buprenorphine-Mono-Product or Buprenorphine-Combined-
11 with-Naloxone; and
12 (b) 201 KAR 20:065, Professional standards for prescribing Buprenorphine-
13 MonoProduct or Buprenorphine-Combined-with-Naloxone by APRNs for
14 medication assisted treatment for opioid use disorder.
15 (2) Contrary provisions of any section of the Kentucky Revised Statutes
16 notwithstanding, the administrative regulations and any proposed amendments to
17 the administrative regulations referenced in subsection (1) of this section shall be
18 null, void, and unenforceable as of the effective date of this Act.
19 (3) Contrary provisions of any section of the Kentucky Revised Statutes
20 notwithstanding, the administrative bodies shall be prohibited from promulgating
21 administrative regulations that are identical to, or substantially the same as, the
22 administrative regulations and any proposed amendments to the administrative
23 regulations referenced in subsection (1) of this section.
24 (4) The administrative regulations and any proposed amendments to the
25 administrative regulations referenced in subsection (1) of this section shall be
26 available to the public, in the office of the Legislative Research Commission's
27 regulations compiler.
