1 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 311 IS CREATED TO
2 READ AS FOLLOWS:
3 (1) Notwithstanding any state law or administrative regulation to the contrary, the
4 State Board of Medical Licensure shall not promulgate any administrative
5 regulation that restricts or limits the prescribing, dispensing, or administering of
6 buprenorphine-mono-product, buprenorphine-combined-with-naloxone, or any
7 other Schedule III, IV, or V medication approved by the United States Food and
8 Drug Administration for the treatment of a substance use disorder.
9 (2) Subsection (1) of this section shall not prohibit the board from promulgating or
10 enforcing administrative regulations in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A that
11 apply to the prescribing, dispensing, or administering of all controlled substances
12 in one (1) or more schedules of controlled substances, including but not limited to
13 201 KAR 9:260.
14 SECTION 3. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 313 IS CREATED TO
15 READ AS FOLLOWS:
16 (1) Notwithstanding any state law or administrative regulation to the contrary, the
17 Kentucky Board of Dentistry shall not promulgate any administrative regulation
18 that restricts or limits the prescribing, dispensing, or administering of
19 buprenorphine-mono-product, buprenorphine-combined-with-naloxone, or any
20 other Schedule III, IV, or V medication approved by the United States Food and
21 Drug Administration for the treatment of a substance use disorder.
22 (2) Subsection (1) of this section shall not prohibit the board from promulgating or
23 enforcing administrative regulations in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A that
24 apply to the prescribing, dispensing, or administering of all controlled substances
25 in one (1) or more schedules of controlled substances, including but not limited to
26 201 KAR 8:540.
27 SECTION 4. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 314 IS CREATED TO
