13 SECTION 5. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 315 IS CREATED TO
14 READ AS FOLLOWS:
15 (1) Notwithstanding any state law or administrative regulation to the contrary, the
16 Kentucky Board of Pharmacy shall not promulgate any administrative regulation
17 that restricts or limits the prescribing, dispensing, or administering of
18 buprenorphine-mono-product, buprenorphine-combined-with-naloxone, or any
19 other Schedule III, IV, or V medication approved by the United States Food and
20 Drug Administration for the treatment of a substance use disorder.
21 (2) Subsection (1) of this section shall not prohibit the board from promulgating or
22 enforcing administrative regulations in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A that
23 apply to the prescribing, dispensing, or administering of all controlled substances
24 in one (1) or more schedules of controlled substances.
25 Section 6. Whereas it is essential that the General Assembly promptly provide
26 effective access to drugs and medicines in the Commonwealth in order to provide for the
27 health and safety of citizens, an emergency is declared to exist, and this Act takes effect
